title: Live: Maddinson falls after Blues fly past 50
text:
Matador Cup final live: New South Wales v South Australia coverage from North Sydney Oval FOX SPORTS Matador Cup final live: New South Wales v South Australia coverage from North Sydney Oval FOX SPORTS Moises Henriques takes one-handed stunner 0:29 
Matador Cup: Moises Henriques has taken a one-handed stunner for New South Wales in their One Day Cup final against South Australia at North Sydney Oval. October 25th 2015 an hour ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/Cricket/Highlights/ 
South Australia has set New South Wales a target of 222 to win in the Matador Cup final at North Sydney Oval. 
After losing the toss and being sent into bat, the Redbacks got off to an awful start, losing Travis Head for one in the first over to a Mitchell Starc yorker. 
The South Australia skipper was joined by Tim Ludeman in the sheds five overs later, with the opener caught in the slips off Josh Hazlewood for seven. ODD2015-160301 
The wicket of Head saw Starc equal Shane Harwood for the scalps most in a one-day domestic season, but he didn’t break the record until the 46th over when he knocked over Joe Mennie for nine. He took his wicket-tally for the season to 26 with the scalp of Kane Richardson four balls later. 
Starc and the Blues were made to toil for much of the innings thanks to a 154-run stand from centurion Tom Cooper (105) and Callum Ferguson. 
Ferguson made a patient 61 from 87 before falling to Stephen O’Keefe (1-53), triggering a batting collapse. From 3-166 in the 37th over, the Redbacks were all out in the 47th. Other Stories
